Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses a higher-order generalization of the graph Laplacian, which is a fundamental tool in graph algorithms and spectral graph theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with the Laplacian on graphs, which can be viewed as a discrete analogue of the Laplace-Beltrami operator on surfaces in computational geometry. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper may be of interest to researchers studying network analysis and community detection, as the Hodge Laplacian has been used in these areas. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the numerical computation of the Hodge Laplacian and its eigenvalues, which is a topic of interest in numerical linear algebra. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper may be relevant to researchers studying graph games and graph algorithms, as the Hodge Laplacian has been used in these areas.
